{"id":"quant-ph/0006116","submitter":"Ulrich Mohrhoff","authors":"Ulrich Mohrhoff","title":"Objective probabilities, quantum counterfactuals, and the ABL rule","comments":"Submitted to American Journal of Physics; v1 responds to\n  quant-ph/0003098v3, v2 responds to Kastner's revised submission; 32 pages,\n  LaTeX2e","journal-ref":"Am J Phys 69(8) 864-873 (2001)","doi":"10.1119/1.1371920","report-no":"SAAPS 000612","categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  The ABL rule is derived as a tool of standard quantum mechanics. The\nontological significance of the existence of objective probabilities is\ndiscussed. Objections by Kastner and others to counterfactual uses of the ABL\nrule are refuted. Metaphysical presumptions leading to such views as Kastner is\ndefending in her Comment are examined and shown to be unwarranted.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Jun 2000 02:43:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 21 Feb 2001 04:37:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-06"}
{"id":"quant-ph/0006117","submitter":"Daniel Braun","authors":"Daniel Braun, Fritz Haake, Walter T. Strunz (Fachbereich Physik,\n  Universit\\\"at-GH Essen)","title":"Universality of Decoherence","comments":"4 revtex pages, no figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. Lett. {\\bf 86}, 2913 (2001)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevLett.86.2913","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We consider environment induced decoherence of quantum superpositions to\nmixtures in the limit in which that process is much faster than any competing\none generated by the Hamiltonian $H_{\\rm sys}$ of the isolated system. While\nthe golden rule then does not apply we can discard $H_{\\rm sys}$. By allowing\nfor simultaneous couplings to different reservoirs, we reveal decoherence as a\nuniversal short-time phenomenon independent of the character of the system as\nwell as the bath and of the basis the superimposed states are taken from. We\ndiscuss consequences for the classical behavior of the macroworld and quantum\nmeasurement: For the decoherence of superpositions of macroscopically distinct\nstates the system Hamiltonian is always negligible.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Jun 2000 13:33:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-06"}
